  "text": "Model C. A constant phase element (Q 2 ) is used to represent the transfer of the charged particles within the passive film, shown in Figure 5 (c). It is believed that the passive film has capacitive characters. Jamnik et al. [CITATION_1] postulate that, in the Nyquist plot, the diffusion of the charged particles in a solid must be combined with a reaction impedance that may result in a slope greater than 45",
